bib_record.title: Elastic, inelastic, and 1-nucleon transfer channels in the 7Li + 120Sn system

free_txt: Homi Bhabha National Institute
Pelletron accelerator facility
Six telescopes (delta E - E) of
Si-surface barrier detectors, T1-T6, each placed 10
degree apart at a distance of ~ 21 cm from the center
of scattering chamber, were used to detect the
projectile - like fragments in angular range of 25 to
140 degree.
Two single Si-surface barrier detectors used
as monitor detectors, fixed at 20 and 30 degree with
regard to the beam at a distance of ~ 39 cm from the
center of the scattering chamber, were used for flux
normalization. The detector thicknesses were
typically 25 to 50 um for delta E and ~ 1000 um for
the E detectors.
The statistical errors on the elastic
scattering cross sections are typically 1 - 2% over
the entire angular range, at extreme backward angles,
it ranges between 4 and 5% for both energies
